    THIS FILE'S ROLE IN THE OVERALL POC
    ===================================
    This is a `sys_report` record of type `single_score` with `aggregate=COUNT`.
    It is the data source for a single tile on the Manager View dashboard
    (../dashboards/pa_dashboards_x_casemgmt_manager_view.xml) showing the
    rolling count of new cases opened in the trailing 30-day window. Its
    purpose is to give managers a glanceable indicator of incoming case
    volume - a leading-edge KPI that complements the lagging-edge
    "Average Time to Close" tile authored at
    ../reports/x_casemgmt_avg_time_to_close.xml.

    SOURCE-SIDE SEMANTIC ANCHOR (AAP SECTION 0.2.1.1)
    =================================================
    The semantic ancestor of this report in the existing ArkCase codebase
    is `CaseSummaryByStatusAndTimePeriodDto.java` at:

        acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-case-file-plugin/src/main/
        java/com/armedia/acm/plugins/casefile/model/
        CaseSummaryByStatusAndTimePeriodDto.java

    That DTO holds `(timePeriod, caseByStatusDtoList)` - a time-bucketed
    aggregation shape that ArkCase's Pentaho-backed reporting layer used
    to render time-window case rollups. The ServiceNow target collapses
    that DTO + Pentaho pipeline into a native `sys_report` whose filter
    expression encodes the time bucket directly via the platform's
    GlideSystem function `gs.daysAgoStart(30)`. No DTO, no Pentaho, no
    Solr facet - the platform's native GlideAggregate engine satisfies
    the requirement directly.

    The supporting field `opened_date` is materialized in
    ../dictionary/x_casemgmt_case_opened_date.xml and auto-populated on
    insert via ../business_rules/x_casemgmt_set_opened_date.xml per AAP
    Section 0.4.1 directory enumeration. Without that auto-set business
    rule, all cases would have NULL opened_date values and this report
    would return 0; the cross-dependency is documented below.

